text:
**Meta Started Hiring with AI Interviews now, Use AI during Interviews ğŸ¤¯**

Meta just made LeetCode grinding obsolete. They're letting you use AI during interviews now...ğŸ’¯ For all the ongoing or upcoming Hiring, one of Meta's coding rounds is now AI-assisted. You get 60 minutes in CoderPad with AI built right into the editor. Pick between GPT-4o mini, Claude Sonnet 4, Gemini 2.5 Pro, or Llama 4. Switch between them mid-interview if you want. You're not solving LeetCode mediums on a blank screen anymore. They give you a multi-file codebase. Fix bugs, add features, handle edge cases.ğŸ¤¯ 

ğŸ“ŒThe AI can write boilerplate, suggest solutions, and catch syntax errors. But you're still evaluated on problem-solving, code quality, and communication.

 Traditional interviews tested if you could write perfect code in 20 minutes without help. That's not how engineering works anymore. 

Zuckerberg said by 2025, Meta will have AI that can effectively be a mid-level engineer. If AI writes half your production code, interviews should test if you can lead that AI, not compete with it.ğŸŒ 

ğŸ‘‰ğŸ» Most students are still grinding 500 LeetCode problems alone in a room. That prepares you for 2020 interviews, not 2026.

 ğŸ‘‰ğŸ» You need to practice using AI as a tool while explaining your decisions under pressure. Verify AI code for correctness. Navigate multi-file codebases. Communicate your thought process while the AI assists. [Final Round AI](https://www.linkedin.com/company/finalroundai?trk=public_post-text) helps simulate exactly this. You practice technical interviews with AI assistance built in, get feedback on how you're using AI as a tool and learn to articulate decisions while AI generates code in real-time. The skill isn't "can you code without AI?" anymore. It's "can you lead with AI?" Are you still grinding LeetCode alone or practicing AI-assisted interviews?

**Linkbuilder (Outreach specialist)
**
We are Proxy-Seller, a European product IT company that has been in the web data industry since 2014, offering proxy services for automation, parsing, marketing, and cybersecurity. Our mission is to help businesses worldwide achieve their goals through high-quality IP solutions.

Communicating with webmasters, negotiating placements, and ensuring smooth cooperation.

Maintaining reports and keeping an up-to-date database of acquired links.
Monitoring indexing, link performance, and the quality of placed backlinks.

Excellent self-organization and the ability to manage several tasks and campaigns simultaneously.

Employee referral program.
Opportunity to work with competitive Tier-1 niches and develop advanced outreach skills.
